# AGENTS.md

## Project

Go API server + React dashboard. Postgres 16, migrations via Liquibase.
Monorepo managed with Make at the root and pnpm workspaces for the frontend.

## Commands

- Build: `make build` (never `go build` directly, it skips codegen)
- Unit tests: `make test`
- Integration tests: `make test-integration` (needs Docker running first)
- Lint: `make lint` before every commit
- Frontend dev server: `pnpm --filter web dev`

## Key modules

- `/internal/store` - all database access. Nothing else touches the DB.
- `/internal/api` - HTTP handlers. Keep them thin. Logic lives in `/internal/service`.
- `/internal/service` - business logic. This is where most changes land.
- `/migrations` - Liquibase changelogs. Append only, never edit old files.
- `/web` - React dashboard. Separate pnpm workspace with its own conventions.

## Patterns

- Wrap errors with context: `fmt.Errorf("load user: %w", err)`. No naked `return err`.
- Every new endpoint needs a handler test AND a service test.
- Feature flags go through `flags.IsEnabled()`. Never read env vars in business logic.
- New DB queries belong in `/internal/store`, exposed through an interface.

## Never touch

- `/internal/api/gen` - generated from the OpenAPI spec. Run `make gen` instead.
- Old files in `/migrations` - append a new changelog file.
- `go.sum`, `pnpm-lock.yaml` - let the tools manage them.
